mobilize /ˈməʊbɪˌlaɪz/

(mobilizing,mobilized,mobilizes) 

1. V-T/V-I If you mobilize support or mobilize people to do something, you succeed in encouraging people to take action, especially political action. If people mobilize , they prepare to take action. 动员; 动员起来 

例： The best hope is that we will mobilize international support and get down to action. 最大的希望就是我们将动员国际社会的支持，开始行动。 

2. mobilization N-UNCOUNT 动员 

例： ...the rapid mobilization of international opinion in support of the revolution. …对支持革命的国际舆论的迅速动员。 

3. V-T If you mobilize resources, you start to use them or make them available for use. 调动 

例： If you could mobilize the resources, you could get it done. 如果你能调动资源，你就能完成它。 

4. mobilization N-UNCOUNT 调动 

例： ...the mobilization of resources for education. …调动教育资源。 

5. V-T/V-I If a country mobilizes , or mobilizes its armed forces, or if its armed forces mobilize , they are given orders to prepare for a conflict. 动员 (军队); (国家军事力量) 动员起来 [journalism] 

例： Sudan even threatened to mobilize in response to the ultimatums. 苏丹甚至威胁说要动用军事力量来回应最后通牒。 

6. mobilization N-UNCOUNT (军事) 动员 

例： ...a demand for full-scale mobilization to defend the republic. …全面动员来保卫共和国的命令。

